The paper deals with extracting key information from documents using NLP techniques and neural networks. The proposed model, CUTIE, applies convolutional neural networks on gridded texts, which is a common technique used in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also mentions the use of Named Entity Recognition (NER) method, which is a common technique in natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also deals with structured data and automation, which falls under information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.CV and cs.CL, followed by cs.IR, cs.LG, and cs.AI.
